 {"id":"bd-3vbf.14","title":"Visual Effects: Add Matrix Rain Effect","description":"## Background

The visual_effects.rs already has impressive effects but is missing the iconic Matrix digital rain. beads_viewer mentions this as one of the effects:
- Streaming characters falling at variable speeds
- Brightness gradient from white (head) to green (tail)
- Random character mutations
- Column-spawning with wrap-around

Matrix rain is instantly recognizable and impressive.

## Implementation

```rust
struct MatrixColumn {
    x: usize,
    chars: Vec<(char, f64)>,  // char + brightness
    speed: f64,
    y_offset: f64,
}

struct MatrixRainState {
    columns: Vec<MatrixColumn>,
    katakana: Vec<char>,  // Character set
}

impl MatrixRainState {
    fn update(&mut self) {
        for col in &mut self.columns {
            col.y_offset += col.speed;

            // Fade existing chars
            for (_, brightness) in &mut col.chars {
                *brightness *= 0.95;
            }

            // Add new char at head
            if rand_simple() < 0.3 {
                let new_char = self.katakana[rand_range(0, self.katakana.len())];
                col.chars.insert(0, (new_char, 1.0));
            }

            // Random mutations
            for (c, _) in &mut col.chars {
                if rand_simple() < 0.1 {
                    *c = self.katakana[rand_range(0, self.katakana.len())];
                }
            }

            // Trim old chars
            col.chars.retain(|(_, b)| *b > 0.05);
        }
    }

    fn render(&self, painter: &mut Painter, width: u16, height: u16) {
        for col in &self.columns {
            for (i, (c, brightness)) in col.chars.iter().enumerate() {
                let y = (col.y_offset as i32 - i as i32) % height as i32;
                if y >= 0 {
                    let green = (brightness * 255.0) as u8;
                    let color = PackedRgba::rgb(0, green, 0);
                    // Render character at (col.x, y)
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

## Character Set

Use half-width katakana and Latin for authenticity:
ｱｲｳｴｵｶｷｸｹｺｻｼｽｾｿﾀﾁﾂﾃﾄﾅﾆﾇﾈﾉﾊﾋﾌﾍﾎﾏﾐﾑﾒﾓﾔﾕﾖﾗﾘﾙﾚﾛﾜﾝ

